Sculpture by the Sea returns to the Bondi to Tamarama coastal walk from Friday 21 October to Monday 7 November. Local road closures will be in place each day of the event from 7:30am to 6:30pm.

Significant delays are expected on roads approaching the area during the event, particularly on weekends. Motorists should avoid the area where possible or allow plenty of extra travel time on Bondi Road, Old South Head Road and Syd Einfeld Drive approaching Bondi Beach. 

Special event clearway parking restrictions will be in effect along both sides of Bondi Road each weekend of the event on Saturday 22 and Sunday 23 October, Saturday 29 and Sunday 30 October, and Saturday 5 and Sunday 6 November:

  • 7am to 2pm: Bondi Rd from Oxford St at Bondi Junction to Sandridge St at Bondi Beach.
  • 12pm midday to 8pm: Bondi Rd from Sandridge St at Bondi Beach to Oxford St at Bondi Junction.

Clearways are strict no-parking zones for all vehicle types, and apply even to local residents and TfNSW Mobility Scheme Permit holders. Check signs carefully as vehicles left in clearways will be towed and a fee applies. If your vehicle is towed it will be relocated to the nearest legal parking space, use the Find My Car website or call 132 701 to find its new location.

The closest station to Shellharbour Airport is Albion Park on the South Coast Line.

Shellharbour Airport is opposite the station on the Princes Highway. Event staff and traffic controllers will be on site to assist attendees crossing the highway, take care and follow the directions of staff.

Across the weekend all South Coast trains stopping at Albion Park between 8am and 6pm will be built up to 8 carriages. All services arriving and leaving from Albion Park between 7:30am and 1:30pm will stop on platform 1.

To help you get home, additional services will leave Albion Park at 2:55pm, 3:50pm and 4:50pm stopping at Dapto, Unanderra, Coniston, Wollongong, North Wollongong, Thirroul, Helensburgh, Waterfall, Sutherland, Mortdale Hurstville, Wolli Creek, Redfern, Central then all stations to Bondi Junction.

Alternatively consider using station car park facilities and continuing your trip by train to Albion Park. The following stations have car parking facilities on the South Coast Line: Waterfall, Helensburgh, Stanwell Park, Austimer, Thirroul, Bulli, Corrimal, Towradgi, Fairy Meadow, North Wollongong, Wollongong, Oak Flats, Shellharbour, Dapto and Bombo.

properties.otherAdvice:
Up to 10,000 cyclists will ride from Sydney to Fairy Meadow for the 40th annual MS Gong Ride. The 79km ride from Tempe Recreation Reserve starts from 6am and the 52km ride will start at Preston Park, Engadine from 8am. Both events finish at Thomas Dalton Park in Fairy Meadow by 4pm.

Road and lane closures will be in place along sections of the course.

  • 4am to 9:30am from Tempe to Sutherland: sections of West Botany St, Holbeach Ave and Bestic St. The speed limit will be reduced to 60/km along Rocky Point Rd/Taren Point Rd from Sans Souci to Taren Point.
  • 5am to 9:30am from Sutherland to Waterfall: Lane closures southbound on the Princes Hwy from Kirrawee to Loftus and the speed limit will be reduced to 60km/h from Kirrawee to Waterfall. Delays are expected travelling southbound on the Princes Hwy during this time. 
  • 5am to 2:30pm in the Royal National Park: McKell Ave, Lady Wakehurst Dr, Sir Bertram Stevens Dr and Otford Rd. Sections of Lawrence Hargrave Drive at Stanwell Tops and Domville Rd at Otford will also closed. Access to the Royal National Park is via Farnell Ave at Loftus only.
  • 5am to 4.30pm in Fairy Meadow: sections of Elliotts Rd near the finish area will be closed. The speed limit will be reduced to 40km/h along Lawrence Hargrave Dr from Stanwell Park to Thirroul from 6am to 3pm.

Motorists should exercise caution as cyclists will be sharing some roads along the course. Motorists are reminded when overtaking cyclists to leave a 1.5m distance on roads with speed limits over 60km/h and a 1m distance on roads 60km/h or under.

Special event clearways will be in place along key sections of the course between 4am and 3pm. Clearways are strict no-parking zones for all vehicle types, and apply even to local residents and TfNSW Mobility Scheme Permit holders. Check signs carefully as vehicles left in clearways will be towed and a fee applies. If your vehicle is towed it will be relocated to the nearest legal parking space, use the Find My Car website or call 132 701 to find its new location.

properties.otherAdvice:
More than 800 trucks and 900 motorbikes will form part of the annual i98 Illawarra convoy travelling from Appin and Bulli Tops to finish near Shellharbour Airport in Albion Park Rail. Motorbikes will leave from West Cliff Colliery, Appin from 8:15am, trucks will leave from Maddens Plains at 8.30am.

The convoy will travel via Appin Rd, Old Princes Hwy, M1 Princes Mwy, Masters Rd, Five Islands Rd, King St, Windang Rd, Shellharbour Rd, Lake Entrance Road, New Lake Entrance Rd and Princes Hwy. The convoy will finish at the Convoy shop, corner of Airport Rd and Princes Hwy, Albion Park Rail. Bikes will arrive from 9.15am and trucks from 10am.

Motorists may experience traffic delays along the convoy route. 

Speed reductions will be in effect at various times and locations between 4.30am and 3pm on sections of Appin Rd, M1 Princes Mwy and Princes Hwy.

The Old Princes Highway at Madden Plains will be closed between Helensburgh and Maddens Plains while trucks form up to participate in the convoy.

The right hand turn from Old Mount Ousley Rd onto the M1 Princes Mwy/Mount Ousley Rd will be closed between 7am and 12pm. The convoy will travel in one lane along the route. 

Motorists are advised to take care as they share roads with the convoy vehicles and allow extra travel time in the area while changed traffic conditions are in place.
